Concept for Life Large Puppy & Junior has been specially developed to optimally support the unique nutritional needs of growing puppies and junior dogs of large breeds (adult weight 26-44 kg).

Concept for Life offers optimised, scientifically based nutrition.

Product advantages:

Brain development
The omega-3 fatty acids contained in salmon oil can support normal brain development and increase learning ability.
Harmonious growth
The balanced protein content and moderate energy intake can promote even growth and minimise the risk of excessive weight gain during the prolonged growth phase of large dogs.
Bones and teeth
The increased vitamin D3 content and the balanced ratio of calcium and phosphorus support optimum bone and tooth development during the growth phase. The formula also contains the two natural cartilage components glucosamine and chondroitin sulphate.
Support for the body's natural defences
The special vitamin and antioxidant complex with aronia berries, hops and green tea can strengthen the body's defences and support the immune system during the growth phase.

Excellent acceptance and tolerability
The balanced recipe with fresh meat and high-quality ingredients ensures optimum acceptance, even with fussy puppies.
Well-balanced nutrients
This recipe provides all the essential proteins, fatty acids, vitamins and minerals required for optimum all-round nutrition.
Dental care
The special structure of the kibble can support dental hygiene.

.

This scientifically based formula promotes optimal development during the critical growth phase and supports your dog's vitality.

Available in the sizes: 1.5kg, 6kg, 12kg and 24kg.

Taste of the Wild – Sierra Mountain is a natural, easy to digest dry dog food for dogs of all sizes, breeds and in the adult stage of life. Chicory with the prebiotic inulin and yucca schidigera help to keep the digestive system working well. Lukullus Barbary Duck & Lamb is complete dry dog food formulated to meet your dog’s nutritional needs:

In harmony with nature: Natural recipes with carefully selected ingredients for dogs with gourmet tastes
Natural flavours Cold-pressing helps to retain the original flavour and natural nutrients

Milk thistle seeds help to detox the liver
Linseed is good for a healthy metabolism, skin and shiny fur

Lukullus dry dog food Barbary Duck & Lamb with potatoes is gently cold-pressed using the very best, selected ingredients. The cold pressing process helps the food to retain its natural flavour and essential nutrients. No artificial additives are necessary because nature provides everything that your dog needs.

Lukullus dry food recipes have been lovingly crafted using only top-quality ingredients which appeal to the palates of dogs with good taste. Succulent Barbary Duck meat is defined by its strong flavour and is also very easy to digest. New Zealand Lamb is known for its tenderness and both deliver important animal protein. Combined with potatoes and fruits such as pear, apple and blueberry, Lukullus dry food delivers an optimal combination of essential vitamins and minerals that your dog needs. The enriching nutritious oils help to improve the health of your dog’s coat and skin. Lukullus only contains natural preservatives. It is gluten-free and no GM ingredients are used.

What is cold-pressing?
In contrast to conventional manufacturing methods, cold pressing avoids high temperatures and high pressure during the processing stage. This helps to preserve as many essential nutrients as possible and makes this food easy for your dog to digest.

Lukullus - trust in the power of nature.

Store in a cool, dry place. Do not store in airtight containers. Lukullus try to keep all products as natural as possible so no artificial additives such as preservatives, colour or attractants are added. Therefore these cold-pressed foods only have a minimum shelf life of 8 months from date of production.

product_name: Concept for Life Veterinary Diet Dog Renal
ingredients_raw:
Low in protein and phosphorus, this therapeutic complete dry food is suitable for adult dogs with chronic renal insufficiency. It can help to reduce calcium oxalate and uric acid stone formation.

Concept for Life Veterinary Diet Dog Renal at a glance:

Dietetic complete dry food tailored to your dog's specific nutritional needs
Scientifically-based nutrition which supports veterinary therapy
Top-quality raw ingredients ensure it is well-accepted, and very digestible
Made in Germany

Concept for Life Veterinary Diet – Renal is a premium complete dry food for adult dogs with kidney issues. Impaired renal function can compromise the kidney's abilities to perform efficiently. Toxins and protein wastes are not fully eliminated, and the kidneys become overloaded. If your dog is suffering from kidney disease it needs a diet that helps to relieve and support the kidneys. Insufficient or low fluid intake combined with a hostile, acidic urinary environment can lead to the formation of bladder stones such as calcium oxalate or uric acid stones. The appropriate mineral content and urinary pH values can help to reduce the risk of bladder stones.

How can Concept for Life Veterinary Diet Renal dry food help your dog?
This premium dietetic dry food has been specifically developed for dogs with renal problems and is optimally adapted to suit their nutritional needs. It has a low protein content and is made using only top-quality protein which produces fewer toxins and waste products such as urea. It is also low in phosphorus which helps to reduce the work the kidneys must do. Dogs with renal problems are often unable to eliminate excess phosphorus and this can overload the kidneys. This tasty food is also low in calcium, vitamin D and purine, which helps to reduce formation of calcium oxalate and uric acid kidney stones. A balanced ratio of minerals helps to counteract over-acidic urine. Dogs with kidney disease often suffer from loss of appetite. Concept for Life Veterinary Diet – Renal is well accepted.

Concept for Life Veterinary Diet – tailored therapeutic nutrition for your dog.

Contraindications:
Not suitable for pregnant or lactating dogs, puppies, dogs with hepatic insufficiency associated with impaired bile secretion.

Our quality guarantee:

Very well accepted, made with high-quality raw materials
Made in Germany

product_name: bosch Special Light Dry Dog Food
ingredients_raw:
High-quality kibble for dogs with kidney problems. Wheat-free recipe with a reduced protein and mineral content. Helps to relieve strain on the metabolism and prevent urinary gravel and kidney stones.

bosch Special Light Dry Dog Food is the perfect wheat-free diet for adult dogs that suffer from liver or kidney problems. It contains reduced levels of protein and minerals, and has been specially developed to relieve strain on your dog's metabolism and help to prevent urinary gravel and kidney stones. The added immune complex contains mannans and beta glucans to help stabilise your dog's gut flora and strengthen their immune system.

Adult dogs that suffer from problems with their urinary system (kidneys and ureter) or liver metabolism require a special diet designed to reduce metabolic waste products, thereby relieving strain on these organs. Thanks to its extremely low protein content (13%), composed of high-quality proteins, as well as the food's reduced mineral levels (incl. phosphorous, sodium and magnesium), bosch Special Light complete dog food is suitable for long-term feeding. This wheat-free kibble is made from specially selected ingredients, which are carefully processed to preserve their delicious taste. For extra peace of mind, the products of animal origin are sourced exclusively from animals fit for human consumption.

A mixture of naturally-occurring tocopherols have been added to bosch dog food to help conserve the delicate yet essential vitamins and fatty acids. You can rest assured that with bosch quality dog foods, you will always be able to find the right nutrition for your dog’s needs.

ingredients_raw:
Well accepted wet food for dogs with kidney problems, including chronic renal insufficiency. Designed to ease pressure on the kidneys, with antioxidants and EPA/DHA.

General information:

Please seek your vet's advice before using this food or extending the feeding period.
When feeding your dog with a veterinary diet you should consult your vet regularly for check-ups.
If your dog's health deteriorates please seek veterinary advice immediately.

Royal Canin Renal Loaf Wet Dog Food has been designed in response to the prevalence of chronic renal insufficiency (CRI) in dogs, which can often manifest itself in anorexia (loss of appetite). In cases of CRI, feeding a specially adapted diet is especially important. Royal Canin Renal moist dog food is a dietetic wet food that has been especially developed for dogs with kidney illness. The food can help to support kidney function and contains a special antioxidant complex as well as essential EPA and DHA and has a lower phosphorus content.
The food’s adapted protein content helps to prevent overloading of the kidneys and the alkalizing formulation helps to balance the dog’s metabolism. The flavours in the food have been selected to be particularly appealing to dogs, to help to make the food as well accepted as possible.

Recommended for (indications):

Chronic renal insufficiency (CRI)

Not recommended for (contraindications):

Hyperlipidemia
Pancreatitis or recovery after acute pancreatitis
Lactating bitches, pregnant bitches or puppies

Key benefits:

Dietary management of chronic renal complaints: Recipe designed to support renal function in cases of chronic renal disease. With EPA and DHA, an antioxidant complex and low phosphorus.
Eases strain on the kidneys: Excess pressure on the kidneys can lead to urine poisoning, whereas food with a balanced protein content can help to ease the load on the kidneys.
Balanced metabolism: Chronic renal complaints can cause metabolic acidosis. The alkalizing formula of this moist dog food can help to counteract this effect.
Acceptance: Selected ingredients create a flavour profile that is very well accepted.

Duration of treatment:
It is recommended to start feeding a special diet as early as possible. It is advisable to use special foods for the rest of the dog’s life, in cases of chronic renal disease.

Rocco Diet Care Renal is a meat-based dietetic wet dog food that supports renal function. This great-tasting food is a complete therapeutic wet dog food suitable for adult dogs with impaired kidney function. It is low in protein and phosphorus and made using only top-quality, easy to digest animal proteins.

This recipe is formulated to meet the nutritional needs of dogs with acute or chronic kidney insufficiency. If your dog has kidney illness it is important to feed a low-protein diet with reduced levels of sodium and phosphorus, as many of these ingredients can have a detrimental effect on kidney function. For this reason, this wet food contains only limited sources of top-quality animal protein, all of which are very digestible and easy to digest. Beef and chicken offal provide valuable energy without overloading the kidneys and the sodium and phosphorus content has been deliberately reduced to further encourage kidney relief. Vital vitamins and nutrients round off this delicious, meaty wet dog food and provide your pet with a balanced, nutritional meal.

product_name: Concept for Life Veterinary Diet Weight Control
ingredients_raw:
Low carb dietetic nutrition for overweight adult dogs, this complete dry dog food can help to regulate the glucose supply and supports a healthy weight. Suitable for dogs with diabetes mellitus.

Concept for Life Veterinary Diet Weight Control is a premium complete dry food for adult dogs with weight problems. Obesity in dogs can have several causes. Some of the main reasons are too little exercise and too high energy intake. Neutered dogs are also prone to weight increase due to their reduced metabolism. If your dog is overweight it can increase the risk of certain diseases such as diabetes mellitus, a disorder where an insufficient insulin function affects the glucose metabolism. A change to your dog's diet is necessary to support weight reduction and to regulate the glucose supply.

How can Concept for Life Veterinary Diet Weight Control help your dog?
This premium therapeutic kibble has been specifically developed to meet the nutritional needs of dogs that are overweight or suffer from diabetes. Natural dietary fibre promotes the feeling of satiety and a regular digestion. If your dog is overweight its joints can be particularly stressed. Glucosamine and chondroitin sulphate provide nutrients that can help to support cartilage. The low carbohydrate content helps to regulate the glucose supply if your dog is suffering from diabetes mellitus. Concept for Life Veterinary Diet Weight Control provides your dog with all important vitamins, minerals and trace elements, so your pet will not suffer any nutrient deficiency, even if it remains on this diet for a long time.

Concept for Life Veterinary Diet – tailored therapeutic nutrition for your dog.

ingredients_raw:
Dietetic wet food for adult dogs with food intolerances, dermatosis and hair loss. This vet food can be used as an exclusion or elimination diet as kangaroo is the only source of animal protein.

Concept for Life Veterinary Diet Hypoallergenic - Kangaroo at a glance:

Dietetic complete wet food tailored to your dog's specific nutritional needs
Scientifically-based nutrition which supports veterinary therapy

Top-quality raw meat ingredients ensure it is well-accepted, and very digestible
Made in Germany.

Concept for Life Veterinary Diet Hypoallergenic - Kangaroo is a premium complete wet food for adult dogs which suffer from nutritional sensitivities. Food intolerances refers to all abnormal physiological reactions after consumption of a food or additive. There is a clear distinction between food allergies and food intolerances.

Food allergies are an overreaction of the immune system to certain proteins. Food intolerances are not caused by the immune system. Both food allergies and food intolerances can lead to skin and digestive problems, such as itching and diarrhoea. An elimination diet will help to determine any food intolerance, The prerequisite for an elimination diet is that the food only contains a selected protein and carbohydrate source. Skin issues are not just caused by intolerance to certain foods but also a reaction to flea saliva or the environment. A diet with top quality fatty acids helps to support healthy skin..

How can Concept for Life Veterinary Diet Hypoallergenic help your dog?
This premium therapeutic food has been specifically developed to meet the nutritional needs of dogs that suffer from food intolerance and dermatosis. In order to reduce the possibility of raw ingredient and nutrient intolerance the only source of protein in this food is kangaroo and parsnips are the only source of carbohydrates. Excluding commonly used animal protein and commonly used carbohydrates from your pet's diet helps to lessen the risk of an adverse reaction. This food is enriched with thistle oil and linseed oil, both of which are particularly high in omega-3 fatty acids.

Concept for Life Veterinary Diet – tailored therapeutic nutrition for your dog.

ingredients_raw:
Wheat-free dog food for puppies up to 4 months old. With at least 30% fresh poultry, as well as colostrum and green-lipped mussel extract. Boasts an immune complex with ß-glucans and mannans.

bosch Puppy Dry Dog Food is the perfect wheat-free diet for puppies up to 4 months of age. It has been specially developed to meet your young dogs' nutritional needs during the weaning phase, and can be fed to puppies from 3 weeks old if soaked in water. It boasts 30 % fresh poultry, as well as a special immune complex containing mannans and beta glucans, which works alongside the added colostrum to help stabilise your dogs' gut flora and strengthen their immune system.

It is important to play special attention to your puppies' nutrition, particularly during the weaning phase, when their enzymatic digestive system needs to adjust from their mother's milk to solid food. bosch Puppy complete dog food is made from specially selected ingredients, which are carefully processed to preserve their delicious taste. For extra peace of mind, the products of animal origin are sourced exclusively from animals fit for human consumption.

A mixture of naturally-occurring tocopherols have been added to bosch dog food to help conserve the delicate yet essential vitamins and fatty acids. You can rest assured that with Bosch quality dog foods, you will always be able to find the right nutrition for your dog’s needs.

Rocco Diet Care Hypoallergenic is a complete dietetic wet dog food which can help reduce the effects of food and nutrient intolerances. It contains only carefully selected, limited sources of protein and carbohydrates. It is rich in essential fatty acids and supports skin function in dogs suffering from dermatosis and excessive hair loss caused by food sensitivities.

This hypoallergenic meat-based therapeutic wet food is formulated to meet the specific nutritional needs of dogs suffering from nutrition-related issues such as allergies or food intolerances. These can cause vomiting and diarrhoea, as well as dermatosis, itching and hair loss. To alleviate these symptoms your dog needs a diet which is adapted to its nutritional requirements. This tasty recipe contains only ingredients with a low allergenic potential. It is made using just one source of animal protein – lamb. This helps to minimise any food intolerance. It is completely grain-free and the only vegetable it contains is easy-to-digest pumpkin. Fish oil is a great source of omega 3 and 6 fatty acids which help to reduce skin reactions.

The main growth and development phase for medium-sized breeds predominantly takes place during the first six months of your puppy’s life. In order to grow into a healthy adult dog, you should avoid diets with excessive calcium, as well as feeding your puppy too much or too little at mealtimes. A healthy diet should contain a balanced mix of vital nutrients, as well as an adapted content of essential carbohydrates, proteins, fats, vitamins and minerals, all of which help your puppy to lead a long and healthy life. Pregnant and lactating dogs have similar nutritional needs as puppies, so also benefit from a diet with increased energy, protein, vitamins and minerals.

Concept for Life Medium Junior is a dry dog food formulated to suit the needs of medium breed puppies up to 12 months of age. It provides your puppy with a balanced diet for optimal all-round care, as well as meeting specific growth requirements.

Concept for Life Medium Junior meets the specific nutritional requirements of puppies and growing dogs. The adapted protein content is easy for your puppy to digest and is combined with a balanced mix of vital nutrients. The increased vitamin D3 content and the well-balanced ratio of calcium and phosphorus help to promote consistent development of bones and teeth. The special FORMULA X actively supports life-long health and can help to keep your puppy in good shape. Concept for Life combines lots of carefully selected fresh meat, which are sources of high-quality protein, with functional ingredients to create a balanced mix of premium nutrients. The resulting kibble is easy to digest and well accepted.

This tasty puppy kibble also contains a vitamin-B-complex which, in combination with copper, organically-bound zinc, as well as high-quality omega-3 and omega-6 fatty acids, can help to promote glossy fur and supple skin. This food also supports optimal joint and cartilage development during this important growth phase.

Concept for Life is a unique and scientific-based nutritional concept, which focuses on your dog’s individual well-being and dietary requirements at different life stages. The variety Medium Junior provides your medium-sized growing puppy with a balanced nutrition.

Concept for Life Veterinary Diet Gastrointestinal is a premium complete wet food for adult dogs with inadequate digestion, disturbed pancreatic function and acute absorption disorders. These dogs do not digest food sufficiently, so they can't absorb nutrients properly. The intestinal flora is disturbed, vomiting and diarrhoea can cause further loss of body water and vital electrolytes. The mucous membranes in the gastrointestinal tract can also become irritated. If these symptoms occur over a long period of time, they can lead to dehydration and emaciation. If your dog has a pancreatic disfunction such as exocrine pancreatic insufficiency these symptoms may be analogous.

How can Concept for Life Veterinary Diet Gastrointestinal support your dog?
Concept for Life Veterinary Diet Gastro Intestinal is a specially developed high-premium dietary complete food for adult dogs, which is optimally adapted to the nutritional needs of dogs with inadequate digestion and impaired pancreatic function. Palatable ingredients include turkey meat and offal, pumpkin and salmon oil, all of which are easy to digest so that your dog's digestive system is not overloaded. Feed this food in small portions for optimal compatibility. The increased ratio of selected minerals helps to quickly compensate for any loss of electrolytes. This supports your dog's well-being. The high liquid content in this wet food boosts your dog's fluid intake, helping to prevent dehydration. It is suitable if your dog is suffering from acute or chronic diarrhoea. Concept for life Veterinary Diet Gastrointestinal also contains mannan-oligosaccharides and salmon oil which is rich in omega 3 fatty acids. This helps to build up the disturbed gut flora and has an anti-inflammatory effect. This tasty dog food is low in fat which is important if your pet is suffering from exocrine pancreatic insufficiency.

Concept for Life Veterinary Diet – tailored therapeutic nutrition for your dog.

General information:

Please seek your vet's advice before using this food or extending the feeding period.
When feeding your dog with a veterinary diet you should consult your vet regularly for check-ups.
If your dog's health deteriorates please seek veterinary advice immediately.

What is cold-pressing?
Unlike normal manufacturing processes, cold-pressing does not use high temperatures or pressure. This means that most of the valuable nutrients are preserved and can be utilised by your dog.

Lukullus - trust in the power of nature!

Lukullus dry food recipes have been lovingly crafted using only top-quality ingredients which appeal to the palates of dogs with good taste. What is cold-pressing?
In contrast to conventional manufacturing methods, cold pressing avoids high temperatures and high pressure during the processing stage. This helps to preserve as many essential nutrients as possible and makes this food easy for your dog to digest.

Lukullus - trust in the power of nature.

Store in a cool, dry place. Do not store in airtight containers. Lukullus try to keep all products as natural as possible so no artificial additives such as preservatives, colour or attractants are added. Therefore these cold-pressed foods only have a minimum shelf life of 8 months from date of production.

product_name: Concept for Life Veterinary Diet Renal
ingredients_raw:
Dietetic wet food for adult dogs with chronic renal insufficiency. The therapeutic food has a low phosphorus and protein content to help reduce formation of bladder stones and make urine more alkaline

Concept for Life Veterinary Diet – Renal is a premium complete wet food for adult dogs with kidney issues. When renal function is impaired it compromises the kidney's abilities to perform efficiently. Toxins and protein wastes are not eliminated properly, and the kidneys become overloaded. If your dog is suffering from kidney disease it needs a diet that relieves and supports the kidneys. Insufficient or low fluid intake combined with an acidic urinary environment can lead to the formation of bladder stones such as calcium oxalate or uric acid stones. The appropriate mineral content and urinary pH values can help to reduce the risk of bladder stones.

How can Concept for Life Veterinary Diet – Renal help your dog?
This premium therapeutic food has been specifically developed for adult dogs with renal problems and is optimally adapted to suit their nutritional needs. It has a low protein content and is made using only top-quality protein which produces fewer toxins and waste products such as urea. It is also low in phosphorus which helps to reduce the work the kidneys must do. Dogs with renal issues are often unable to eliminate excess phosphorus and this can overload the kidneys. This tasty food is also low in calcium, vitamin D and purine, which helps to reduce formation of calcium oxalate and uric acid kidney stones. A balanced ratio of minerals helps to counteract over-acidic urine. Dogs with kidney disease often suffer from loss of appetite. Concept for Life Veterinary Diet – Renal is well accepted.

Concept for Life Veterinary Diet – tailored therapeutic nutrition for your dog.

Contraindications:
Not suitable for pregnant or lactating dogs, puppies, dogs with hepatic insufficiency associated with impaired bile secretion.

Dietetic complete wet food tailored to your dog's specific nutritional needs
Scientifically-based nutrition which supports veterinary therapy
Grain-free recipes
No wheat, corn or soya
Top-quality raw meat ingredients ensure it is well-accepted, and very digestible
Made in Germany.

product_name: Wolf of Wilderness Trial Pack: Dry & Wet Food
ingredients_raw:
Wolf of Wilderness dog food: Based on the natural diet of wolves in the wild, try this trial pack of 12kg Wolf of Wilderness Dry Food with either 6 x 400g or 800g Wet Food Cans at a great price!

We can all agree that our dogs are important members of the family – they faithfully stand by our side every single day and therefore deserve a diet that is nutritious and species-appropriate. The domesticated dog originates from the wolf; the natural diet of wolves in the wild is primarily carnivorous and that has remained unchanged throughout the course of evolution. Wolf of Wilderness recognises the importance of providing dogs the diet dictated by their genes and have therefore developed dry and wet food that reflects your dog’s instinctive nutritional needs. Research into the natural feeding habits of wolves has shown that their diet consists primarily of meat, with some wild fruit, herbs and roots. Wolf of Wilderness also ensures that their range is 100% grain-free, as wolves rarely consume carbohydrates in the wild.

Formulated with at least 61% pure meat, the only other ingredients in Wolf of Wilderness dry food are wild herbs, fruits of the forest and roots. The protein-rich kibble combines fresh chicken with lamb or duck, which is easy for your dog to digest. The only source of carbohydrates present in the dry food is potatoes, which provide your dog with natural carbohydrates. They are also fat-free and rich in important trace elements and fibre. The wild herbs, fruits of the forest and roots in Wolf of Wilderness kibble provide essential minerals and secondary plant compounds – this incudes cranberry, raspberries, elderberries and blackcurrants, combined with dandelion roots and herbs like mugwort, St. John’s wort, nettle leaves, chamomile, common yarrow and coltsfoot.
Wolf of Wilderness is a complete dog food for adult dogs of all breeds and sizes.
Wolf of Wilderness – Wild and Free!

Choose from the following Wolf of Wilderness dry food varieties:

‘Green Fields’ Lamb: You are guaranteed to be feeding your dog with all the valuable proteins he needs with this rich lamb and chicken kibble. This dry food is delicious and easily digested.
‘Wild Hills’ Duck: This tender duck meat is rich in easily digestible proteins. The combination with fresh chicken makes this dry food ideal for gourmets!

Lukullus Cold Pressed Chicken with Trout is a premium complete dry dog food. It provides your pet with a great-tasting, balanced meal, packed with vital nutrients. The cold pressing process helps the food to retain its natural flavour and essential nutrients. No artificial additives are necessary because nature provides everything that your dog needs.

Lukullus dry food recipes have been lovingly crafted using only top-quality ingredients which appeal to the palates of dogs with good taste. Tender chicken meat is rich in animal proteins and trout is source of protein and omega 3 fatty acids. They are combined with brown rice and fruits such as pears and apples. Lukullus dry food delivers an optimal combination of vitamins and minerals. The enriching nutritious oils contribute to the health of your dog’s coat and skin. This dry dog food is easy to digest and only contains natural preservatives.

What is cold-pressing?
In contrast to conventional manufacturing methods, cold pressing avoids high temperatures and high pressure during the processing stage. This helps to preserve as many essential nutrients as possible and makes this food easy for your dog to digest.

Lukullus - trust in the power of nature.

Store in a cool, dry place. Do not store in airtight containers. Lukullus try to keep all products as natural as possible so no artificial additives such as preservatives, colour or attractants are added. Therefore these cold-pressed foods only have a minimum shelf life of 8 months from date of production.

ingredients_raw:
For dogs that love good food, high-quality dog food with hearty Angus beef and tender duck, wholegrain rice and apples, natural recipe, carefully cold-pressed, for adult dogs

Lukullus Dog Food Angus Beef & Duck is complete dry dog food that is perfectly tailored to your dog’s needs:

In harmony with nature: a natural recipe with carefully selected ingredients for any dog that loves good food
Authentic flavour and natural nutrients thanks to the delicate cold-pressing process
High-quality protein from first-rate meat: tender Angus beef and delicate duck
Naturally preserved, free from genetically modified ingredients, gluten-free
High-quality complete food for adult dogs of any breed or size
Helps to clean the teeth thanks to its carefully designed kibble shape
Produced in Germany with care

Lukullus Angus Beef & Duck is a dry food made from carefully cold-pressed specially selected natural ingredients. The cold-pressing process means that the ingredients’ original flavours and valuable nutrients are preserved. Nature provides everything that your dog requires.

This lovingly prepared Lukullus dry food recipe will spoil any dog that loves good food with its exceptional ingredients:

The delicate Angus beef meat is of particularly high quality which is evident through its intense flavour. It is combined with tender duck meat to provide essential protein in a food that is very well-liked and easily digestible. The wholegrain rice and the fruit and vegetables including apples, potatoes and fennel in Lukullus’ recipe provide your dog with essential vitamins, minerals and trace elements. Topped off with high-quality white fish oil and rapeseed oil, Lukullus supports shiny fur and smooth skin. Lukullus is lovingly produced in Germany and is gluten-free.
What is cold-pressing?

Cold-pressing is unlike common manufacturing processes in that it doesn’t involve high temperatures or excessive pressure. This means that the valuable nutrients are preserved as much as possible and can be easily absorbed.

Lukullus – trust in the power of nature.

Store in a cool, dry place. Do not store in an airtight container. We aim to produce products that are as natural as possible, therefore, we do not use artificial additives such as preservatives, colourings or flavour enhancers. All of our cold-pressed varieties have a shelf life of only 8 months from the time of manufacturing.

product_name: Bewi Dog Basic
ingredients_raw:
Balanced dry food for adult dogs with normal activity, optimised protein/energy ratio, with meat in food-grade quality, without soy & wheat, TÜV-tested

Bewi Dog Basic is a balanced dry food for adult, normally active dogs. This all-round food is characterised by best acceptance and an optimised protein-energy ratio, with a protein content of 23.5% and a moderate fat content of 11%. This tasty dog food is produced in Germany and contains a high proportion of food-grade poultry, which ensures easy digestibility and valuable proteins. Bewi Dog Basic is free from wheat and soya, as these ingredients have an increased allergenic potential and are often the trigger for intolerances

Bewi Dog Basic contains a highly functional ingredient, brewer's yeast. This offers a variety of health-promoting properties and also ensures a good taste. Immune and vital substances as well as ß-glucans extracted from the yeast cell wall ensure strong defences. These stimulate the body's defences in a natural way and thus ensure the development of an intact immune system. Brewer's yeast has prebiotic MOS, which can have a positive effect on the intestinal flora and the entire digestion. Together with lecithin, it can also improve the health of the skin and coat and promote a shiny coat.

Bewi Dog Basic at a glance:

Complete food for adult dogs with normal activity levels
Made in Germany
70% animal protein, 30% vegetable protein
Optimised protein/energy ratio: 23.5% protein, 11% fat
Food-grade meat: provides high-quality protein for healthy muscle development
Without wheat & soya: reduces the allergenic potential of the feed, for good tolerance
With functional brewer's yeast

Strengthens the body's defences: immune and vital substances, ß-glucans from the yeast cell wall stimulate the body's defences in a natural way and ensure the development of an intact immune system
Support of the intestinal flora: MOS, special cell wall components, promote positive bacteria in the intestine, form a kind of biofilm over the intestinal mucosa and thus act against the spread of negative bacteria
Skin & Coat: Natural complex of various nutrients such as W vitamins and trace elements, together with lecithin can promote the utilisation of essential fatty acids and fat-soluble vitamins, promotes shiny coat

Without artificial additives, with natural antioxidants

product_name: Brit Premium Adult Large Chicken
ingredients_raw:
Protein-rich complete food for adult large breed dogs. Particularly easy to digest, rich in chicken (45%), antioxidants and chondroprotectants for stable joints

Adult dogs of large breeds (25-45 kg) need healthy joints and strong bones due to their high weight. The complete food Brit Premium Adult Large Chicken provides your pet with lots of protein and energy in particularly high quality, supporting strong muscles and a firm skeleton.

Antioxidants and the ingredients glucosamine and chondroitin also help to maintain strong joints. Brit Premium Adult Large Chicken enhances the absorption of healthy fatty acids, slowing the progression of many age-related conditions. The supply of prebiotics improves the microflora of the intestine and the activity of your dog's digestive organs. The high proportion of chicken (45%) provides a high protein content and ensures energy, vitality and longevity. Salmon oil and brewer's yeast support the vitality and activity of the brain and significantly improve the skin and coat quality of your dog. Because Brit Premium Adult L contains no soya, chemical additives or preservatives and uses only natural ingredients, it tastes particularly good even for demanding dogs.

Brit Premium Adult Large Chicken at a glance:

High-quality complete food for large breed adult dogs (25-45 kg)
Best digestibility also for pregnant and nursing bitches
High chicken content (45%) as a source of protein for energy and healthy growth
Herbal extracts and fruits for better taste and high digestibility
Rich in vitamins, minerals and organic micro-elements for a balanced diet
Fructo-oligosaccarides improve intestinal flora and calcium digestion
Mannan-oligosaccharides support immunity development
Prebiotics to boost immunity and metabolism
Omega-3 & Omega-6 fatty acids for a healthy nervous system and good learning ability
Brewer's yeast and salmon oil as natural sources of defence-boosting antioxidants
Yucca extracts reduce faecal odour and bind unpleasant smells already in the intestine
No use of soya, chemical additives and preservatives

Brit Premium Adult Large Chickenis produced in a private family business that has specialised in the development, production and distribution of pet food since 1994.

product_name: bosch Soft Duck & Potato HPC Dry Dog Food
ingredients_raw:
Balanced semi-moist, single protein dog food, for dogs with food intolerances. Grain-free, with carbohydrate from potato. Soft kibble.

bosch HPC Soft Duck & Potato is a balanced and complete dry dog food, which is very well suited to dogs that have sensitive digestion or food intolerances, as well as pickier eaters. With a single source of protein, it is also ideal for dogs whose digestion reacts to eating more than one type of meat or fish at a time. The croquette-shaped kibble is semi-moist, which means that they have a high residual moisture content and are therefore softer than traditional dry dog food. The food has an extra-special flavour, so that even picker dogs will happily eat it. The kibble contains potato, which is easy to digest and acts as a good source of carbohydrate and energy. No grains have been added, as dogs with sensitive digestion can have trouble digesting grain or react badly to it. The premium ingredients produced and carefully processed in the Baden-Württemberg region of Germany make bosch HPC Soft Duck & Potato a high-quality, natural dog food, that will provide your dog with all of the essential nutrients it needs.
The premium duck meat used in this product has a strong flavour that dogs love. Duck is high in quality proteins and minerals, and is also less likely to cause allergic reactions than other meats. Glucosamine and chondroitin can help to build and maintain cartilage, and strengthen bones. Chicory provides prebiotic Inulin, to help to support the intestines and balance gut flora.

bosch HPC Soft Duck & Potato dry dog food at a glance:

For fully grown dogs with sensitive digestion
Ideal for those who have intolerances or allergies to different ingredients
Semi-moist: Soft kibble with a high residual moisture level. Great-tasting, even for pickier dogs
Single-Protein: Only one source of animal protein, to reduce the likelihood of reactions
Grain-free: Uses potato as a rich source of carbohydrate and energy that is easy on the digestion. Rich in Potassium
Duck: A quality source of proteins and minerals, with a distinctive taste and low potential for allergic response
Premium ingredients from Germany’s Baden-Württemberg Region
Glucosamine & Chondroitin: Support the maintenance and functioning of cartilage, especially in joints, and can help to strengthen bones
Chicory: Provides prebiotic Inulin that can prevent the spread of harmful gut bacteria, and help to balance gut flora.
Careful manufacturing processes: To help to preserve nutrients, vitamins and proteins, ensuring the product is easy to digest.

bosch dry dog food only uses carefully selected ingredients (including poultry, whole egg, beef, lamb, vegetables), that are gently processed to produce tasty, wholesome, digestible, high-quality dog nutrition. The animal proteins in bosch foods only come from animals that have been declared fit for human consumption.

A mixture of naturally occurring tocopherols have been added to bosch dry dog food, to help to conserve delicate yet essential vitamins and fatty acids. You can rest assured that with bosch quality dog foods, you will always be able to find the right nutrition for your dog’s needs.

product_name: Brit Premium Adult Medium Chicken
ingredients_raw:
Protein- and energy-rich complete food for adult dogs of medium-sized breeds. Highly digestible with extra chicken meat (45%), rich in antioxidants, fibre, omega 3 & 6

Dogs are man's best friends and of course also his helpers. Medium-sized breeds (10-25 kg) in particular often support us in our daily work, so they need an intact digestive system. Brit Premium Adult Medium Chicken is a high-quality dry food that provides medium-sized dogs with the right amount of vitamins, fibre and prebiotics to keep their organism healthy.

The high proportion of chicken (45%) ensures an optimal protein intake and thus energy, vitality and longevity. Because medium-sized dog breeds are very active animals with a good ability to learn, they need a food rich in omega-3 and -6 fatty acids. This is because they support the nervous system and contribute to optimal brain development and activity. They also improve skin and coat quality and support wound healing as they protect your dog's organism. The ingredients brewer's yeast and salmon oil also provide your pet with antioxidants, strengthening the immune system. The use of natural flavours, herbal and fruit extracts and the absence of soy, chemical additives and preservatives makes Brit Premium Adult Medium Chicken tasty even for picky dogs.

Brit Premium Adult Medium Chicken at a glance:

High-quality complete food for adult dogs of medium-sized breeds (10-25 kg)
Best digestibility also for pregnant and lactating bitches
High chicken content (45%) as a source of protein for energy and healthy growth
Herbal extracts and fruits for better taste and high digestibility
Rich in vitamins, minerals and organic micro-elements for a balanced diet
Fructo-oligosaccarides improve intestinal flora and calcium digestion
Mannan-oligosaccharides support immunity development
Prebiotics to boost immunity and metabolism
Omega-3 & Omega-6 fatty acids for a healthy nervous system and good learning ability
Brewer's yeast and salmon oil as natural sources of defence-boosting antioxidants
Yucca extracts reduce faecal odour and bind unpleasant smells already in the intestine
No use of soya, chemical additives or preservatives

Brit Premium Adult Medium Chicken is manufactured in a private family business that has specialised in the development, production and distribution of pet food since 1994.

product_name: bosch Adult Mini Poultry & Millet Dry Dog Food
ingredients_raw:
Gluten-free dry food for small-breed adult dogs, with at least 30% fresh poultry and green-lipped mussel extract. Also boasts an immune complex with ß-glucans and mannans for stress resistance.

bosch Mini Adult Poultry & Millet Dry Dog Food is the perfect gluten-free diet for adult small-breed dogs weighing up to 15kg. It contains at least 30 % fresh poultry and at least 20% millet for a great taste that will also appeal to fussy dogs. The special immune complex contains mannans and beta glucans to help stabilise your dog's gut flora and strengthen their immune system.

Small-breed dogs have a tendency to be particularly fussy eaters and require a dry dog food with small kibble. bosch Mini Adult Poultry & Millet complete dog food is made from specially selected ingredients, which are carefully processed to preserve their delicious taste. For extra peace of mind, the products of animal origin are sourced exclusively from animals fit for human consumption.

A mixture of naturally-occurring tocopherols have been added to bosch dog food to help conserve the delicate yet essential vitamins and fatty acids. You can rest assured that with bosch quality dog foods, you will always be able to find the right nutrition for your dog’s needs.

bosch Mini Adult Poultry & Millet Dry Dog Food at a glance:

High-quality complete dry food for small-breed adult dogs
Ideal for sensitive dogs: with millet (20%) in place of grain containing gluten
Small kibble: delicious taste and also suitable for fussy dogs
At least 30% fresh poultry: a high-quality source of animal protein
Gluten-free: completely free from wheat and wheat middlings, as well as other grains containing gluten
Added immune complex with ß-glucans and mannans: stabilises your dog's gut flora, strengthens the immune system, improves their resistance to stress and promotes general wellbeing
Green-lipped mussel extract: naturally rich in chondroitin and glucosamine to support joint repair, as well as the development and maintenance of healthy joint cartilage
Chicory: source of inulin, which can have a prebiotic effect and helps to prevent the spread of pathological bacteria in the gut, thereby supporting good bacteria and contributing to a balanced gut flora
Linseeds: rich in omega-3 fatty acids to promote healthy skin and coat, as well as mucins to support digestion and relieve allergy symptoms in a natural way
Organic zinc compounds (zinc chelate): helps improve the body's ability to utilise zinc, which is important for supple skin and a glossy coat
Balanced fatty acid profile: essential for the health of your dog's natural immune system, as well as to support vitality, supple skin and a smooth coat
Balanced ratio of different soluble dietary fibres: promotes healthy gut flora and balanced digestion
Selected raw ingredients are carefully prepared using a modern manufacturing process to help guarantee digestibility and well-formed stools
Vitamin E and the trace element selenium: vital antioxidants that protect the body's cells from metabolic waste products
